==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin [[irrumare]], from [[ir-]] + [[ruma]] ‘teat’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /ɪɹʊ'meiʃən/

===Noun===
'''irrumation'''
# of a man, active participation in [[oral sex]] as a receiver; insertion of the penis into a partner's mouth, especially violently
#*'''1993''': He had, back in Cambridge, taken one of Jem Follett’s boys for a penny, an envisioned Tom Walsingham in his head like a god and the motion towards '''irrumation''' like a prayer. — Anthony Burgess, ''A Dead Man in Deptford''
#*'''2006''': Anal intercourse is reported in between 6-26% of female complainants, but it is important to remember that there may have been a number of different sexual acts performed by the assailant, including '''irrumation''' (forced oral penetration) or cunnilingus. — Baguley, Kumar & Persad, ''Key Topics in Sexual Health'' (Taylor Francis 2006, p. 56)